- The school year '2020-2021' refers to the academic year starting in August 2020 and ending in July 2021;
- The average assessment score is calculated by summing all the assessment scores and dividing by the number of students;
- The total number of students is the count of unique student IDs for each group.

- "top 2 students" refers to the highest-ranking students based on their assessment scores and the most recent assessment dates;
- "performance metrics" include the percentage of students at different proficiency levels (advanced, proficient, partially proficient, not proficient);
- "averages" are calculated for each subject and grade to provide a benchmark for comparison.

- "shining star" refers to the district with the highest performance;
- "leading the way" means having the highest percentage of schools with over 80% proficiency;
- "the majority of students excel" means the percentage of students performing at the proficient level is greater than 80%.

- "Top-performing students" refers to those with the highest assessment scores in their respective grade and subject;
- "Overall average scores" are the average assessment scores across all top performances;
- "Proficiency percentages" indicate the percentage of students performing at the proficient level in the assessments.

sql:
SELECT school_id, AVG(assessment_score) AS average_assessment_score
FROM student_assessment
GROUP BY school_id;

